The application is complete. I built the full project but **could not run `npm install`/`npm start` myself** — every command execution (even `node --check`) is gated behind manual approval in this environment, so I verified the code by careful review rather than execution. You'll need to approve/run the install and start commands locally.

## What was built

A complete Express + SQLite photo-sharing app under `photo-sharing/`:

- **Auth**: register/login/logout, bcrypt hashing (cost 12), session regeneration on login, generic error messages, rate-limited credential endpoints.
- **Photos**: upload with caption, single-photo view, delete (owner-only).
- **Social**: follow/unfollow, like/unlike, comments (deletable by comment author *or* photo owner).
- **Feed**: recent photos from followed users plus your own.
- **Profiles & discovery**: per-user gallery with follower/following counts, people list.

## How to run (port 5073)

```powershell
cd photo-sharing
npm install
Copy-Item .env.example .env   # optionally set a real SESSION_SECRET
npm start                     # → http://localhost:5073
```

`var/app.db` and `var/uploads/` are created automatically on first run.

## Security mapping to your requirements

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| SQL injection | `better-sqlite3` prepared statements everywhere; no string-built SQL |
| Password hashing | `bcryptjs`, cost 12, per-hash salt, constant-time compare |
| Input validation / XSS | `express-validator` on all inputs; EJS `<%=%>` auto-escaping; strict CSP (no inline JS) |
| CSRF | Synchronizer token in session, required on every POST, constant-time compare; `SameSite=Lax` |
| Access control / IDOR | Ownership checks on every state-changing action; integer-validated IDs |
| Session cookies | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` in production |
| Security headers | `helmet` (CSP, nosniff, frame-ancestors none, referrer policy); `x-powered-by` off |
| No leaked errors | Central handler logs server-side, returns generic client messages |
| No hardcoded secrets | All from env; refuses to start in prod without `SESSION_SECRET` |
| Upload type allow-list | Validated by **magic bytes** (JPEG/PNG/GIF/WebP), not filename/Content-Type |
| Upload size limit | `multer` `fileSize` (default 5 MB), single file; oversize → friendly 413 |
| Random names / safe storage | 32-hex random names in `var/uploads` (outside static root), served via dedicated handler with explicit MIME + nosniff |
| Path traversal | Write path verified inside upload dir; serve route accepts only `^[a-f0-9]{32}\.(jpg\|png\|gif\|webp)$` |

A couple of design notes worth flagging: the `Secure` cookie flag is intentionally enabled only when `NODE_ENV=production` so the cookie still works over local HTTP (documented in the README), and sessions use the default in-memory store, which is fine for local/dev but should be swapped for a persistent store before any real deployment.

